    • implement

      public void implement(Class<?> token, Path root) throws info.kgeorgiy.java.advanced.implementor.ImplerException
      Produces code implementing class or interface specified by provided token. Generated class' name is the same as the class name of the type token with Impl suffix. Generated source code is placed in the subdirectory of the specified root directory. For example, the implementation of the interface List would go to $root/java/util/ListImpl.java
      Specified by:
      implement in interface info.kgeorgiy.java.advanced.implementor.Impler
      Parameters:
      token - type token to create implementation for.
      root - root directory.
      Throws:
      info.kgeorgiy.java.advanced.implementor.ImplerException - when implementation cannot be generated for one of these reasons:
      • Given class is primitive or array.
      • Given class is private.
      • Given class is final class.
      • Given class is Enum.
      • ClassGenerator.generate() failed to generate source

    • compile

      private static void compile(Class<?> token, Path tempDir) throws info.kgeorgiy.java.advanced.implementor.ImplerException
      Compiles .class files for .java files of given Class token.
      Parameters:

      tempDir - directory with related .java files.
      Throws:

      • getClassPath(Class) failed to getting classPath.
      • Compiler exit code is not 0.

    • implementJar

      public void implementJar(Class<?> token, Path jarFile) throws info.kgeorgiy.java.advanced.implementor.ImplerException
      Produces jar file implementing class or interface specified by provided token.

      During implementation creates temporary folder with generated .java and .class files. Informs user if fails to delete temporary folder.

      Specified by:
      implementJar in interface info.kgeorgiy.java.advanced.implementor.JarImpler
      Parameters:
      token - type token to create implementation for.
      jarFile - generated jar file path.
      Throws:
      info.kgeorgiy.java.advanced.implementor.ImplerException - when implementation cannot be generated for one of these reasons:
      • Failed to create temporary directory.
      • Failed to implement given Class token in implement(Class, Path)
      • Failed to compile generated sources in compile(Class, Path)
      • The problems with I/O occurred during implementation.
